ntent":"**Network connectivity**: Verify CDN is accessible"},"355":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-119","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#icon-not-loading","content":"**Check browser console**: Look for network errors"},"356":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-120","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#icon-not-loading","content":"**Fallback content**: Provide placeholder content for loading states"},"357":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-121","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#performance-issues","content":"For performance optimization:"},"358":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-122","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#performance-issues","content":"**Preload common icons**: Consider preloading frequently used icons"},"359":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-123","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#performance-issues","content":"**Use sprite mode**: For repeated icons, consider sprite mode which consolidates multiple icons into a single SVG sprite sheet, reducing DOM size and improving performance when the same icon appears multiple times"},"360":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-124","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon#performance-issues","content":"**Minimize icon sets**: Only load icons that are actually used"},"361":{"id":"/docs/components/field","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"page","content":"Field primitives","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field"},"362":{"id":"/docs/components/field-0","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"Composable primitives (Field, FieldLabel, FieldGroup, FieldError) for building form fields"},"363":{"id":"/docs/components/field-1","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#usage","content":"Usage"},"364":{"id":"/docs/components/field-2","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#fieldgroup-props","content":"FieldGroup props"},"365":{"id":"/docs/components/field-3","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#basic-example","content":"Basic example"},"366":{"id":"/docs/components/field-4","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#composition","content":"Composition"},"367":{"id":"/docs/components/field-5","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#positioning-controls-inside-the-group","content":"Positioning controls inside the group"},"368":{"id":"/docs/components/field-6","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"States"},"369":{"id":"/docs/components/field-7","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#examples","content":"Examples"},"370":{"id":"/docs/components/field-8","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#leading-control","content":"Leading control"},"371":{"id":"/docs/components/field-9","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#trailing-control","content":"Trailing control"},"372":{"id":"/docs/components/field-10","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#icon-accessories","content":"Icon accessories"},"373":{"id":"/docs/components/field-11","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**Composition primitives.** The field components (TextField, NumberField, DateField, Select, RadioGroup, CheckboxGroup) compose these internally — reach for those first. These primitives are also the building blocks for custom composite fields, e.g. an input and a select sharing one bordered box."},"374":{"id":"/docs/components/field-12","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"The field decoration is split into granular, composable pieces so the same structure is shared across every field:"},"375":{"id":"/docs/components/field-13","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`Field`** — stacks a field's label, control, description, and error in one consistently spaced column (pure layout — a `Flex` column with the standard field gap)."},"376":{"id":"/docs/components/field-14","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`FieldLabel`** — names the field and flags whether it's required (wraps React Aria `Label`, rendering an optional `*` indicator)."},"377":{"id":"/docs/components/field-15","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`FieldGroup`** — the bordered box that visually unites a field's controls and reflects their shared focus, disabled, and invalid state. Used only by \"boxed\" fields (TextField, NumberField, Select, DateField); presentationally it is a React Aria `Group`."},"378":{"id":"/docs/components/field-16","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`FieldInput`*&#x2A; / &#x2A;*`FieldTextArea`** — the control the user types into (normalized React Aria `Input`/`TextArea` given antares spacing via `Box`)."},"379":{"id":"/docs/components/field-17","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`FieldButton`** — an actionable control placed inside the box, such as the NumberField steppers or a search submit (a click target within the group)."},"380":{"id":"/docs/components/field-18","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`FieldDescription`** — helper text that explains the field; renders nothing when empty (wraps the antares `Text` with `slot=\"description\"`)."},"381":{"id":"/docs/components/field-19","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`FieldError`** — surfaces the field's validation messages when it is invalid, and nothing when valid (a thin wrapper over React Aria `FieldError`)."},"382":{"id":"/docs/components/field-20","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"`FieldLabel`, `FieldDescription`, and `FieldError` each render `null` when they have no content, so callers pass `label` / `description` / `errorMessage` straight through without guarding."},"383":{"id":"/docs/components/field-21","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#composition","content":"A boxed field composes the primitives inside its React Aria field wrapper. Use\n`Field as={...}` to merge the field wrapper and the layout column into a single\nelement:"},"384":{"id":"/docs/components/field-22","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#composition","content":"A field without a box (RadioGroup / CheckboxGroup) composes `Field` + `FieldLabel` + `FieldError` and omits `FieldGroup`."},"385":{"id":"/docs/components/field-23","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#composition","content":"`FieldGroup` is purely presentational — it renders the styled `Group` and holds no React Aria context. The surrounding field wires value, disabled, and validation state into its controls."},"386":{"id":"/docs/components/field-24","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#positioning-controls-inside-the-group","content":"`FieldGroup` rounds its outer corners from DOM order: the group's CSS rounds the start corners of its **first child** and the end corners of its **last child**, so controls are seamless inside and rounded only at the box edges. Author children in visual order and the rounding follows — no per-control positioning prop. A lone control (a TextField input, a Select trigger) is both first and last, so it rounds both edges. The rules are RTL-safe (they use logical `start`/`end` corners)."},"387":{"id":"/docs/components/field-25","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"The states **disabled**, **readonly**, and **invalid** are applied by the field wrapper (e.g. TextField, NumberField, Select). The group reflects them via data attributes on the group."},"388":{"id":"/docs/components/field-26","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"State"},"389":{"id":"/docs/components/field-27","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"CSS Selector"},"390":{"id":"/docs/components/field-28","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"disabled — Applied when the field wrapper is disabled."},"391":{"id":"/docs/components/field-29","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"`[data-disabled]`"},"392":{"id":"/docs/components/field-30","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"invalid — Applied when the field wrapper is invalid (e.g. validation failed)."},"393":{"id":"/docs/components/field-31","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"`[data-invalid]`"},"394":{"id":"/docs/components/field-32","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"focus — Whether an element within the group has keyboard focus (for focus-ring styling)."},"395":{"id":"/docs/components/field-33","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"`[data-focused]`"},"396":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","type":"page","content":"InlineDrawer","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer"},"397":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-0","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","content":"An in-flow collapsible built on RAC Disclosure. Compose a trigger and content to make an accordion or a sidebar rail."},"398":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-1","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#features","content":"Features"},"399":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-2","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#installation","content":"Installation"},"400":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-3","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#props","content":"Props"},"401":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-4","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#examples","content":"Examples"},"402":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-5","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#basic-usage","content":"Basic Usage"},"403":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-6","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#controlled","content":"Controlled"},"404":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-7","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#sidebar-navigation","content":"Sidebar Navigation"},"405":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-8","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#accessibility","content":"Accessibility"},"406":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-9","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#keyboard","content":"Keyboard"},"407":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-10","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#aria","content":"ARIA"},"408":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-11","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#best-practices","content":"Best Practices"},"409":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-12","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","content":"`InlineDrawerPanel` is the collapsible content for the accordion pattern — a thin wrapper over RAC `DisclosurePanel` that hides when collapsed. The trigger is any component you slot in with `slot=\"trigger\"` — there's no dedicated trigger component."},"410":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-13","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#features","content":"In-flow collapsible built on RAC Disclosure — bring your own trigger via `slot=\"trigger\"`"},"411":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-14","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#features","content":"Animated by default; `animate={false}` disables the transition"},"412":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-15","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#features","content":"`placement` selects the collapse axis (`left`/`right` → width, `top`/`bottom` → height)"},"413":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-16","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#features","content":"Controlled and uncontrolled modes (`isExpanded` / `defaultExpanded` / `onExpandedChange`)"},"414":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-17","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#features","content":"Accordion collapse uses the browser's `hidden=\"until-found\"` for find-in-page"},"415":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-18","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#features","content":"`prefers-reduced-motion` support"},"416":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-19","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#props","content":"The `InlineDrawerPanel` component accepts the following props:"},"417":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-20","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#basic-usage","content":"Put a `<Button slot=\"trigger\">` and an `<InlineDrawerPanel>` inside `InlineDrawer`. The panel hides when collapsed and animates open."},"418":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-21","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#controlled","content":"Use `isExpanded` and `onExpandedChange` to drive state externally."},"419":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-22","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#sidebar-navigation","content":"A rail whose content stays visible when collapsed is a composition, not a mode: drive `isExpanded` yourself, render always-visible children (no `InlineDrawerPanel`), and let `minSize`/`maxSize` size the rail. Use numeric (px) sizes so the width animates; intrinsic keywords like `min-content`/`max-content` fit the content exactly but don't animate."},"420":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-23","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#keyboard","content":"Key"},"421":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-24","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#keyboard","content":"Action"},"422":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-25","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#keyboard","content":"`Enter` / `Space`"},"423":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-26","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#keyboard","content":"Toggle via the slotted trigger"},"424":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-27","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#keyboard","content":"`Tab`"},"425":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-28","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#keyboard","content":"Move focus through the content"},"426":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-29","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#aria","content":"A `<Button slot=\"trigger\">` gets `aria-expanded` + `aria-controls` wired to the `InlineDrawerPanel` automatically (via RAC Disclosure)."},"427":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-30","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#aria","content":"For the sidebar rail, the toggle is your own control (e.g. a `ToggleButton`) — give icon-only buttons an `aria-label`, and the content stays in the DOM and accessible since nothing is hidden."},"428":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-31","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#best-practices","content":"Accordion → `Button slot=\"trigger\"` + `InlineDrawerPanel`. Sidebar rail → controlled state + always-visible children."},"429":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-32","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#best-practices","content":"For the rail, use numeric (px) `minSize`/`maxSize` so the width animates; `min-content`/`max-content` fit the content exactly but won't animate."},"430":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-33","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#best-practices","content":"`placement` does not flip in RTL; the side is decided by document/flex order."},"431":{"id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer-34","page_id":"/docs/components/inline-drawer","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/inline-drawer#best-practices","content":"Don't nest InlineDrawers."},"432":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","type":"page","content":"ListBox","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/listbox"},"433":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-0","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/listbox","content":"ListBox is a selectable collection of items rendered inline. Use it for non-popover pickers, inline lists, or as a building block for higher-level components like Select."},"434":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-1","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/listbox#features","content":"Features"},"435":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-2","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/listbox#installation","content":"Installation"},"436":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-3","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/listbox#props","content":"Props"},"437":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-4","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/listbox#examples","content":"Examples"},"438":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-5","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/listbox#basic","content":"Basic"},"439":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-6","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/listbox#controlled","content":"Controlled"},"440":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-7","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/listbox#multiple","content":"Multiple"},"441":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-8","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/listbox#features","content":"**Single or multiple selection**: Set `selectionMode=\"single\"` or `\"multiple\"`."},"442":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-9","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/listbox#features","content":"**Controlled or uncontrolled**: Use `selectedKeys` and `onSelectionChange` for controlled state, or `defaultSelectedKeys` for uncontrolled."},"443":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-10","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/listbox#features","content":"**Layout primitive**: `ListBox` and `ListBoxItem` accept layout props (`gap`, `padding`, etc.) — they extend `FlexOwnProps`."},"444":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-11","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/listbox#features","content":"**Composes into other components**: `Select` uses `ListBox` internally; reach for `ListBox` directly when you need an inline list rather than a popover dropdown."},"445":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-12","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/listbox#features","content":"**React Aria integration**: Built on React Aria ListBox for accessibility, keyboard navigation, and typeahead."},"446":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-13","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/listbox#features","content":"`ListBox` requires either `aria-label` or `aria-labelledby`. For a labeled, popover-style picker, prefer `Select`."},"447":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-14","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/listbox#props","content":"The ListBox component accepts the following props:"},"448":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-15","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/listbox#basic","content":"Single selection with static children. Use `aria-label` to give the listbox an accessible name."},"449":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-16","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/listbox#controlled","content":"Use `selectedKeys` and `onSelectionChange` for controlled state."},"450":{"id":"/docs/components/listbox-17","page_id":"/docs/components/listbox","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/listbox#multiple","content":"Set `selectionMode=\"multiple\"` to allow multiple values. `selectedKeys` is a `Set<Key>` (or the literal `'all'`)."},"451":{"id":"/docs/components/menu","page_id":"/docs/components/menu","type":"page","content":"Menu","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/menu"},"452":{"id":"/docs/components/menu-0","page_id":"/docs/components/menu","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/menu","content":"Accessible dropdown menu supporting keyboard navigation, nested submenus, and flexible item rendering"},"453":{"id":"/docs/components/menu-1","page_id":"/docs/components/menu","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/menu#installation","