x is fully polymorphic - the `as` prop allows rendering as any HTML element or custom component while preserving type-safe props."},"1325":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-27","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**HTML Elements:** When using `as=\"button\"`, TypeScript enforces button-specific props like `type`, `disabled`, and `onClick`."},"1326":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-28","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**Custom Components:** When using `as={MyComponent}`, Box accepts that component's props. If there's a prop name conflict, Box's props take priority."},"1327":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-29","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**Typed Refs:** Refs are correctly typed based on the `as` value - `useRef<HTMLButtonElement>` works with `as=\"button\"`."},"1328":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-30","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#alignment","content":"Self-alignment props allow Box to position itself within flex or grid containers."},"1329":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-31","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rtl-support","content":"Box uses CSS logical properties (`padding-inline-start`, `padding-block-end`, etc.) which automatically adapt to RTL layouts. No additional configuration is needed."},"1330":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-32","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#design-tokens","content":"All spacing, elevation, and rounding values are derived from the theme. If no theme is provided, default values are used. This ensures consistency across the design system